<section class="tt-section tt-page">
  <div class="tt-inner">

    <div class="tt-section-head">
      <span class="tt-eyebrow">
        <span class="tt-eyebrow-dot"></span>
        Self-hosted &amp; open-source
      </span>
      <h2 class="tt-section-heading">Own everything.</h2>
      <p class="tt-section-lead">
        No subscription tiers locking features. No third-party processor in the middle.
        No SaaS terms deciding what you can do. Your server, your data, your rules.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tt-ownit-grid">

      <div class="tt-ownit-card">
        <div class="tt-ownit-num">01</div>
        <h3>Your data stays yours</h3>
        <p>
          Everything runs on your own server and PostgreSQL database. No external party can
          read, sell, or lose access to your booking data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tt-ownit-card">
        <div class="tt-ownit-num">02</div>
        <h3>One command, or full control</h3>
        <p>
          Use the one-command installer, the Docker Compose stack, or a manual Node deploy —
          whatever fits your infrastructure and skill level.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tt-ownit-card">
        <div class="tt-ownit-num">03</div>
        <h3>Developer API &amp; webhooks</h3>
        <p>
          A documented REST API, signed outgoing webhooks, and an embeddable booking widget
          for integrating Tidetime into your own product.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tt-ownit-card">
        <div class="tt-ownit-num">04</div>
        <h3>MIT licensed</h3>
        <p>
          Free and open under the MIT license. Read the code, fork it, extend it, white-label it,
          and contribute improvements back to the community.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="tt-stats-strip">
      <div class="tt-stat-item">
        <div class="tt-stat-num">9</div>
        <div class="tt-stat-label">feature areas</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-stat-item">
        <div class="tt-stat-num">3</div>
        <div class="tt-stat-label">calendar providers</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-stat-item">
        <div class="tt-stat-num">5</div>
        <div class="tt-stat-label">video providers</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-stat-item">
        <div class="tt-stat-num">1</div>
        <div class="tt-stat-label">command to install</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
